{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-03","name":"Gauthier d'Ath","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Gauthier d'Ath","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Gauthier"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"d'Ath"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"1050–1122","fullLifespan":"1050–avant 1122","portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/q4ecj/thumb200s.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"DOCUMENT","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7709-106405-231-56/dist.pdf?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/123803571","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7709-106405-231-56/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Gauthier d’Ath, Seigneur d’Ath, in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy","description":"Gauthier d’Ath, Seigneur d’Ath, in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy\n~http://shop.fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/HAINAUT.htm#GauthierAthMAdaRoucy","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"DOCUMENT","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7702-106406-654-40/dist.pdf?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/123804627","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7702-106406-654-40/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Wedricus and Thierry, Seigneurs d’Avesnes, in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy","description":"Wedricus and Thierry, Seigneurs d’Avesnes, in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy\n~http://shop.fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/HAINAUT.htm#ThierryAvesnesMIdaRoucy","@type":"ImageObject"},{"memoryType":"DOCUMENT","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7702-106405-138-68/dist.pdf?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/123803345","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7702-106405-138-68/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"Geoffroy de Guise, Seigneur de Guise, in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy","description":"Geoffroy de Guise, Seigneur de Guise, in the Foundation for Medieval Genealogy\n~http://shop.fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/nfravalver.htm#GeoffroyGuisemAdaRoucy","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1050","birthPlace":{"address":"Ath, Hainaut, Belgique","geo":{"latitude":50.629,"longitude":3.7748,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathPlace":{"address":"Roeux, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","geo":{"latitude":50.2965,"longitude":2.8971,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"   GAUTHIER d’Ath, son of ---.  Seigneur d’Ath.  Defossez suggests that Gauthier d’Ath was the same person as Gauthier de Chimay (died “before 1082”), that his son Alard de Chimay (“1088”, died “before 1090”) was born to an unidentified first wife, and that Béatrix d’Ath (wife of Arnoul de Hainaut, see below) was his daughter by his “second” wife Alix de Ramerupt[554].  m as her second husband,  ADA de Ramerupt, widow of GEOFFROY Seigneur de Guise, daughter of HILDUIN [IV] de Montdidier et de Ramerupt Comte de Roucy & his wife Adelaide de Roucy (-bur Abbaye de Liessies).  The Chronicle of Alberic de Trois-Fontaines names \"Ada…de Guisia\" as sixth daughter of Hilduin Comte de Roucy[555].  The Genealogiæ Scriptoris Fusniacensis names \"quartam…Hilduini comitis filiam Adam\" as wife firstly of \"Godefridus de Guisia\" and secondly of \"Galterum de Aat et genuit filias; quarum una tradita est Gerardo de Audenarde, que peperit Arnulfum et Godefridum atque Heinricum et ceteros.\" and thirdly of \"Theoderico de Avesnis\"[556].  She married thirdly Thierry Seigneur d'Avesnes.   Gauthier & his wife had [two or more] children: \n\na)         BEATRIX d’Ath .  The Genealogiæ Scriptoris Fusniacensis refers to \"Guidonem [de Guisia] qui habuit sororem\" whose husband was \"Arnulfo, fratre Balduini comitis Hainonensis\"[557].  The Chronicon Lætiense names \"Arnulpho, fratri comitis de Hainau Balduini\" and his wife \"Beatricem filiam [Waltero de Aat] et Ade [filiam] Eustacii del Rues\"[558].  m ARNOUL de Hainaut, son of BAUDOUIN II Comte de Hainaut & his wife Ida de Louvain (-after 1117). \n\nb)         daughter .  The Chronicle of Alberic de Trois-Fontaines refers to the daughters of \"Galterum de Aat\" & his wife, specifying that one married \"Gerardo de Audenarde, que peperit Arnulfum et Godefridum atque Heinricum et ceteros\"[559].  m GERARD van Oudenaarde, son of ---. \n\nhttp://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/HAINAUT.htm#GauthierAthMAdaRoucy\n\n ","sourceList":[{"title":"Gauthier d'Arth -Medlands - FMG","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"http://fmg.ac/Projects/MedLands/HAINAUT.htm#GauthierAthMAdaRoucy","sourceUri":"QSC8-6TT"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1050","date":"1050","place":"Ath, Hainaut, Belgique"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1075","date":"about 1075","place":"Ath, Hainaut, Belgium","age":"25","id":"G24K-7LN"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1075","date":"1075","place":"Ath, Hainaut, Belgium","age":"25","id":"LK1B-JZ4"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1095","date":"avant 1095","place":"Ath, Hainaut, Belgique","age":"44","id":"GKVC-STC"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1104","date":"après 12 octobre 1104","age":"54","id":"GKVC-XB9"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1119","date":"28 January 1119","place":"Liessies, Nord, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","age":"69","id":"G6GM-G8D"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1122","date":"avant 1122","place":"Roeux, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","age":"71"}],"parent":[{"name":"Wauthier D'ATH","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1030–1122","birthDate":"+1030","deathDate":"+1122","age":92,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree